FBIS4-47967 "drafr089_e_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-089 Daily Report 7 May 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia ULIMO Frontline Commanders Agree to Cease-Fire ULIMO Frontline Commanders Agree to Cease-Fire AB0705154694 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 7 May 94 AB0705154694 Monrovia Radio ELBC English BFN [Text] Krahn and Mandingo frontline commanders of ULIMO [United Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia] have agreed to cease fire [words indistinct]. They have also agreed that all roads within ULIMO-controlled areas be under the control of ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] and be open for free passage for all persons. These agreements were reached yesterday at the end of a meeting between the two groups at ECOMOG headquarters in Monrovia. The joint communique, signed by both groups, also says that the hierarchy of ULIMO leadership will meet in Monrovia Monday [9 May] under the auspices of ECOMOG and UNOMIL [UN Observer Mission in Liberia] to effectively reunite the ULIMO family.
